Serving dishes such as Snail Porridge, Mad Hatter's Tea Party, and Botrytis Cinerea, Heston's success lies in the hands of his Australian diners. As the first critics come to review the Melbourne restaurant, back in England, Heston is looking to the future of the English Fat Duck and masterminding a brand new dining experience.

title: The Gadget Show
desc: Big names like Under Armour and FitBit have released brand-new fridge models which claim to not only track all your fitness stats, but coach you to improve them with apps. Jon hands them out to some couples who all want to either lose weight or shape up - and they'll all keep video diaries to help reveal which one is best. Plus, we unbox the brand-new Ganker Fighting Robots, and Jordan's got the latest breaking news from the world of gaming.

title: The Gadget Show
desc: Three-hundred-and-sixty-degree cameras have been around for a while but have generally failed to impress - mostly because of the glitchy software required to make them work. But two new models from action cam experts GoPro and Garmin might change everything. These models promise better-than-ever software that allows you to edit your own 360-degree masterpiece. Georgie and Ortis test them out during a sightseeing day in Las Vegas, taking in a helicopter ride, a graveyard for neon signs and a zipwire above a street to see which one captures the action best. All that, plus Harry Wallop joins Craig on the sofa with his latest money saving tips.

title: MythBusters
desc: Adam and Jamie test the myth that a ricocheting bullet could kill the shooter in an enclosed space, while Tori, Grant and Jessi make their own tree catapult to investigate the story that trees were used in medieval times to launch diseased bodies over castle walls.

title: The Pizza Show
desc: Frank Pinello has eaten his share of pizza in Manhattan and Brooklyn, but it's time for him to check out New York City's other boroughs - Queens, Staten Island, and the Bronx.

title: The Ice Cream Show

title: Chinese Dating With the Parents
desc: Single hopefuls reach out to the famed Meng Fei for help with their love problems. But there is a catch - any potential partners must go through an intensive and gruelling interrogation with the contestant's parents to proceed to the next stage.

title: Takeshi's Castle
desc: The evil Shogun Takeshi has kidnapped Princess Woonsen and imprisoned her in his castle. Contestants aim to storm Takeshi's castle and free her.

title: The Orville
desc: Ed discovers that Moclans aboard the Orville are harbouring a secret.

title: The Orville
desc: A time distortion affects Ed and Kelly's relationship.

title: 8 Out of 10 Cats Does Countdown
desc: It's Letters and Numbers with a whole bunch of comedians. Hosted by Jimmy Carr, Rachel Riley, and Susie Dent, featuring guests Joe Wilkinson, Sara Pascoe, Josh Widdicombe, and Bill Bailey.

title: Future Man
desc: Using facial recognition technology to figure out where the Pointed Circle is hiding, Stu sends Tiger to a Mons storage facility run by Jeff Breakfast. Though she insists on going alone, once Breakfast identifies a photo of Athena and directs her to a unit where she's been spotted, Tiger is surprised to find Ty-Anne waiting for her.

title: Future Man
desc: Having been outed as a Biotic and abandoned by Wolf, Tiger returns to Stu's lair to drown her sorrows with drugs. Noting that there's more to life than numbing her pain, Stu gives Tiger a device that bursts the shell she's living in, placing her in a simulation where she can realise whatever her mind can imagine.

title: The Handmaid's Tale
desc: Confined in a hospital, June's sanity begins to fray. An encounter with Serena Joy forces June to reassess her recent actions.

title: Shot by Kern
desc: Seasoned photographer Richard Kern, best known for his images of scantily-clad, amateur models, travels around the globe to interview and shoot hundreds of women in their homes and apartments, capturing them even during their most intimate moments, including everything from brushing their teeth topless to lying naked in bed.

title: The Longest Day in Chang'an
desc: Chang'an: the city of eternal peace. China's ancient imperial capital and the world's most magnificent metropolis. Its treasures and wealth are now under siege from a mysterious army. In 24 hours, the enemies will launch a devastating attack. While the nobles panic and flee, the city's most notorious criminal will be its saviour.

title: Like Crazy
desc: A British college student falls for an American student, only to be separated from him when she's banned from the US after overstaying her visa.

title: The Proposition
desc: In rural Australia during the late 1920s, a lawman apprehends a notorious outlaw and gives him nine days to kill his older brother, or else they'll execute his younger brother.

title: Ali's Wedding
desc: Meet Ali, the charming son of a Muslim cleric, who, despite the best of intentions, just can't seem to make the right life choices. Ali dreams big: he wants to be with the girl he loves, but he's been promised to another girl at his father's mosque. He wants to be the great doctor that the community expects him to be, but he doesn't get the marks. And above all, he wants to make his father proud - really proud. So what will Ali do to live up to the impossible expectations? He must fake it, because as the son of the cleric, he doesn't have a choice. It's one bad decision after another as Ali's wayward quest to please his father spirals out of control, with cataclysmic consequences.

title: Strings
desc: A story of war, intrigue and betrayal in a kingdom of wooden puppets.

title: The Tree of Life
desc: Director Terrence Malick traces the evolution of an 11-year-old boy in the Midwest, from his first experiences of joy, love and mercy (from his mother), to his introduction to the 'ways of the world' (from his father). Each parent contends for his allegiance, and the boy must reconcile their claims. His experience of the world, once a thing of glory, becomes a labyrinth as he seeks unselfish love.

title: White Tuft, the Little Beaver
desc: A beaver couple live by their dam. As the seasons go by, they have babies, gather food, maintain their dam, play and swim, and, of course, defend their territory against predators and intruders. After one of their young gets lost in the forest, the mother and father beaver search frantically for him, while he is rescued by an unlikely ally.

title: Born to Dance
desc: A coming-of-age tale told through the eyes of Tu, an ambitious young man from Auckland who dreams of being a professional hip-hop dancer.

title: Yeh Jawaani Hai Deewani
desc: Kabir and Naina bond in college, but before Naina can express her love, Kabir leaves India to pursue his career. In a twist of fate, the two reconnect in their twenties.

title: Lassie
desc: When a financial crisis hits the Carraclough family, they are forced to sell their beloved dog to a local duke, but Lassie isn't happy with her new living arrangements and soon sets out on an 800km journey back to the home she loves.

title: School of Life
desc: In 1920s France, an orphan is adopted by a rustic couple who work for a rural landowner. Left to himself, he soon comes under the spell of the local poacher.

title: Waking Ned Devine
desc: Two elderly Irishmen scheme to claim the winnings of a deceased unlucky villager: he had died of shock after hitting a lottery jackpot.

title: Jane Got A Gun
desc: A woman is forced to turn to an old flame in order to bring justice to the deadly gunslingers responsible for the death of her husband.

title: The Cook and the Chef
desc: From pasta to gelati, tomatoes to octopus - Italian migrants have contributed enormously to our Australian way of life. Maggie's love of Italian opera and food is well known, and she reminisces about her childhood visits with her family to an Italian restaurant in Sydney where she fell in love with pasta.

title: Donal's Cook, Eat, Burn
desc: Donal combines tourism with getting active when he explores the Kerry coastline on a coasteering trip. He prepares food designed to enhance his day of healthy activity, including fudge, coriander fishcakes with a spiralised-veggie Thai salad, spiced Indian dahl, and filo pastry pie.

title: Nigella Express
desc: Nigella's conjuring up dazzling Italian food in a flash from sensational pasta to an entire effortless feast. She cooking, she's shopping, she's entertaining and sharing fabulous fast cooking tips. There's pasta pronto, linguine with a sensational raw sauce of lemon, garlic and thyme mushrooms. Then a fabulous, no stress, no effort anti pasti feast with marsala honey pears and gorgonzola.

title: BBQ Crawl
desc: Danielle and her two favourite barbecue buddies, Randy and Andy, hit up the brightly lit Jack's BBQ in downtown Nashville, Tennessee. It's as much a tourist stop as the Grand Ole Opry. And here, it's all about eatin' like a tourist and ordering it all. Then it's off to Pegleg Porker, where they worship pork - they don't even serve beef on their menu. Danielle and friends dig into some Tennessee dry ribs, barbecue sushi, and their killer pork sandwich. The adventure is capped off at the Music City BBQ Festival in downtown Nashville where they enter a margarita contest, a specialty of Randy and Andy's. Music, booze and competitive spirit are in the air.

title: BBQ Crawl
desc: In rural Tennessee, Danielle visits Helen's BBQ, a place run by a female pitmaster. She's been stacking wood and hauling pigs since 1995. It's nothing fancy, but she serves up the best pulled pork sandwich anywhere in the state, and Danielle is eager to try it. Next, Danielle heads to the Pie Folks, home of the award-winning 'Slap Yo' Mama' chocolate pie. Danielle ends her visit by judging a pie eating contest. Then, we head to the heart of Memphis - Central BBQ, where it's all about barbecue nachos and fried chicken skins. And then it's off to the Bar-B-Q Shop, where the locals eat. The Vernon family opened this place in 1987 and are known for their barbecue spaghetti and famous 'muddy ribs.'.

title: Sicily with Aldo and Enzo
desc: Trapani is a major fishing town and is closer to the coast of North Africa than it is to mainland Italy and, therefore, considering the Arab influence on the region's cuisine it should come as no surprise to find cous cous on the menu. But, before that, Aldo and Enzo prepare an impressive sea bass which is encased in a coat of local sea salt before baking. It's a veritable sea food fest.

title: Gourmet Farmer
desc: Over the last few years, Matthew has discovered his small farm is too shady and too wet for most of the year, which has hindered his farming aspirations. Now, Matthew is upscaling. He has bought a new 70 acre farm 10 minutes away. There is a lot of work to be done: roads to build, fences to repair, and a poly-tunnel and smoker to build. All of this is part of Matthew's grand dream to produce and direct sell his own produce.

title: Peter Kuruvita's Coastal Kitchen
desc: Having bid farewell to city life and moved to the tropical seaside town of Noosa, chef and restaurateur Peter Kuruvita heads out to meet the community of passionate producers, to discover more about the fresh local produce that has made this region one of the most exciting foodie destinations in Australia. Since moving to the Sunshine Coast, Peter and his family haven't looked back. Peter begins his journey by visiting family-owned and run farms in the Sunshine Coast, before transforming their produce into family-friendly dishes, including his own Kuruvita family favourite, pho, using Thai basil picked from his own garden.

title: Food Safari Italy
desc: Maeve joins Claude Basile for black ink pasta, and restaurateur Beppi Polese shows how his famous baccala mantecato is made. In Melbourne, specialist butcher Roger Ongarat explains what makes pork and fennel sausages such a favourite in Italian households. Chef Alessandro Pavoni demonstrates how to make the perfect risotto, and rising star Vanessa Martin shows Maeve how easy and delicious crostoli are to make.

title: Come Dine with Me
desc: Every week, five strangers take it in turns to throw a dinner party. But this is no ordinary supper, as the guests are secretly scoring the host, and at the end of the week the top-scoring host wins 1000 pounds.

desc: Drawing back to her grandmother and other family members, Helani will show and teach us how to make some staple dishes that are made every day in the Torres Strait Islander community.

title: Pati's Mexican Table
desc: Pati heads to the coastal city of Champoton, located an hour south of Campeche. With a warm welcome from her friend Chachi, they taste their way through the local market and gather groceries for a family dinner at Hacienda Niop. Pati learns the secrets behind the area's most prized dishes: pibi pollo, a gigantic tamal cooked underground, and pan de cazon, a local version of lasagna made with corn tortillas, dogfish, beans, and spicy tomato sauce. Back in Pati's kitchen, she makes her own version of the giant tamal, a bit simpler but with all the flavour; these little packets are a party on their own. And to finish it off, something sweet and reminiscent of the seaside village, a creamy crema de coco.

title: River Cottage Australia
desc: Paul welcomes home his jersey cow Bessie but it's not the homecoming he was hoping for - Bessie could be barren. Tomato season has sprung and Paul needs to make the most of his troubled crop. He welcomes two new friends to the farm, with expert passata knowledge passed down by generations. He learns there's more to mushrooms than meets the eye, and takes advantage of the autumn rain by dropping into mate Darcy's to dunk some traps into his dam.

title: Nigella Express
desc: This episode, Nigella cooks up perfect recipes for after-work entertaining such as a fast food processor chocolate cake with a ready-made peppermint syrup drizzle and a DIY dinner. Then, for a casual super speedy supper, Nigella's making crab and avocado salad with a zesty Japanese dressing. Elegant, substantial and ready in minutes.

Aboriginal elder Neville Poelina and his family take him fishing for barramundi at Udialla Springs on the edge of the Western Desert, before Jimmy joins them for an outback supper.

title: The Great Australian Cookbook
desc: Creator of the fine dining institution the Lake House in Daylesford, Victoria, Alla Wolf-Tasker prepares her share platter recipe. Agrarian cook Rodney Dunn showcases his Tasmanian property's produce, baking a rhubarb and berry crumble with goat's milk and vanilla custard for his young family.

title: Jimmy Shu's Taste of the Territory
desc: Jimmy visits the breathtaking landscapes of Kakadu to find out about Top End bush foods that Aboriginal people have been eating for thousands of years. He meets traditional owner Mandy Muir who takes Jimmy to see her country via a boat trip along the spectacular Yellow Waters. Next Jimmy meets young Bininj chef Ben Tyler who runs Kakadu Kitchen.

That evening, Poh serves curry puffs to all her favourite people before they tuck into the pizzas, which are a big success. Fast forward three months and Poh is very excited to be cooking with her first crop of tomatoes.

Police believe that she was held captive and kept alive for around 10 days, during which time she was tortured and sexually abused before being killed. Six months later, bush hikers stumble across Lois' skeletal remains.

title: Sweet Country

Sam and his pregnant wife Lizzie go on the run and a posse pursues them across the outback. The posse don't catch Sam, as he is a clever man and an expert bushman. Eventually, for the health of his pregnant wife, Sam gives himself up. A trial is held in town and when the truth comes out in the courtroom about Sam's actions, he is acquitted. Justice has been served. Philomac and Sam set off on their journey home, but, soon after leaving town, a shot rings out and justice is crushed.

title: Green Bush

This film is a celebration of an era of music, working for a cause and getting things done. But not in the way you would expect.

desc: It's Letters and Numbers with a whole bunch of comedians. Hosted by Jimmy Carr, Rachel Riley, and Susie Dent. Featuring guests Lee Mack, Victoria Coren Mitchell, Alan Carr, and Sam Simmons.

title: Party of Five
desc: As Lucia hopes to get close to Sully following her successful fundraiser, Valentina goes to extremes to keep her dance class in the dark about her family. Beto gets some unsettling news about Ella.

title: Live PD: Police Patrol
desc: The team investigates grand theft auto in Tulsa, a dead body found in South Carolina, and a dangerous foot pursuit in Florida.

title: Live PD: Police Patrol
desc: The squad looks into a gun draw in Florida, a naked foot pursuit in South Carolina, and a gang shooting in Bridgeport.

title: My Extreme Life
desc: Over 6000 people in the UK have dwarfism, and we follow three extraordinary young people who have achondroplasia, the most common form of dwarfism, as they reach major milestones in their lives and find the determination to overcome daily obstacles. Often the simplest of tasks can be a huge challenge as they learn to live in a giant world.

title: The Feed
desc: After a summer of bushfires, floods, and now COVID-19 killing 80 percent of sales, NSW oyster farmers are begging for the government to waive marine fees and charges for fear they will go bust. They're also calling for the same level of assistance that land farmers have received to help manage the impacts of stock loss.

title: Game of Bros
desc: Across cultures there is a tradition of manaakitanga and gift-giving. Inspired by the Samoan tradition of Si'i Alofa, our warriors must carry delicate gifts and create gifts from clay.

title: Ali's Wedding
desc: Meet Ali, the charming son of a Muslim cleric, who, despite the best of intentions, just can't seem to make the right life choices. Ali dreams big: he wants to be with the girl he loves, but he's been promised to another girl at his father's mosque. He wants to be the great doctor that the community expects him to be, but he doesn't get the marks. And above all, he wants to make his father proud - really proud. So what will Ali do to live up to the impossible expectations? He must fake it, because as the son of the cleric, he doesn't have a choice. It's one bad decision after another as Ali's wayward quest to please his father spirals out of control, with cataclysmic consequences.

title: The House by the Sea
desc: By a little bay near Marseille lies a picturesque villa owned by an old man. His three children have gathered by his side for his last days: Angela, an actress living in Paris, Joseph, who has just fallen in love with a girl half his age, and Armand, the only one who stayed behind in Marseille to run the family's small restaurant. It's time for them to weigh up what they have inherited of their father's ideals and the community spirit he created in this magical place. The arrival, at a nearby cove, of a group of boat people will throw these moments of reflection into turmoil.

title: Sweet Country
desc: Set in 1929 in the outback of the Northern Territory, this is the story of a young boy called Philomac, who witnesses Sam, an Aboriginal stockman, kill station owner Harry Marsh in self-defence. Sam and his pregnant wife Lizzie go on the run and a posse pursues them across the outback. The posse don't catch Sam, as he is a clever man and an expert bushman. Eventually, for the health of his pregnant wife, Sam gives himself up. A trial is held in town and when the truth comes out in the courtroom about Sam's actions, he is acquitted. Justice has been served. Philomac and Sam set off on their journey home, but, soon after leaving town, a shot rings out and justice is crushed.

title: School of Life
desc: In 1920s France, an orphan is adopted by a rustic couple who work for a rural landowner. Left to himself, he soon comes under the spell of the local poacher.

title: Lassie
desc: When a financial crisis hits the Carraclough family, they are forced to sell their beloved dog to a local duke, but Lassie isn't happy with her new living arrangements and soon sets out on an 800km journey back to the home she loves.

title: Waking Ned Devine
desc: Two elderly Irishmen scheme to claim the winnings of a deceased unlucky villager: he had died of shock after hitting a lottery jackpot.

title: Spirited Away
desc: Chihiro and her family are on their way to their new house in the suburbs, but on their way, they stumble upon a tunnel that leads them into a fantasy world full of ghosts and strange creatures.

title: Broken Hill
desc: A sheep rancher's son dreams of being accepted into the Sydney Conservatorium of Music. He has trouble finding an adequate band in the outback to perform his compositions, until he comes upon a talented prison choir.

title: Born to Dance
desc: A coming-of-age tale told through the eyes of Tu, an ambitious young man from Auckland who dreams of being a professional hip-hop dancer.

title: Raid
desc: A fearless income tax officer raids the mansion of the most powerful man in Lucknow after an anonymous tip incriminates the feared big shot.

title: Walking Out
desc: An urban teenager journeys to Montana to hunt big game with his estranged father. Father and son struggle to connect, until a brutal encounter in the heart of the wilderness changes everything.

title: No Country for Old Men
desc: Based on the novel by Cormac McCarthy, violence and mayhem ensue after a hunter stumbles upon some dead bodies, a stash of heroin and more than $2 million in cash near the Rio Grande.

title: Jane Got A Gun
desc: A woman is forced to turn to an old flame in order to bring justice to the deadly gunslingers responsible for the death of her husband.

title: The Cook and the Chef
desc: Simon and Maggie go vegetarian, proving a meat-free diet is far from bland and boring. While vegetarianism has always been part of Indian and Asian culture, it didn't really kick off in the west until the mid-19th century.

title: Donal's Cook, Eat, Burn
desc: Donal travels to Antrim to go kayaking on the River Bann. He prepares dishes specially picked to keep him going on the long day ahead, including homemade granola, blueberry and chia seed muffins, poached eggs with za'atar and quinoa, and red lentil and sweet potato soup.

title: Nigella Express
desc: This episode, Nigella cooks up perfect recipes for after-work entertaining such as a fast food processor chocolate cake with a ready-made peppermint syrup drizzle and a DIY dinner. Then, for a casual super speedy supper, Nigella's making crab and avocado salad with a zesty Japanese dressing. Elegant, substantial and ready in minutes.

title: BBQ Crawl
desc: Danielle visits Longoria's BBQ outside of Fort Worth for their famous beef jerky and brisket sausage. In downtown Dallas, we pull up to the Oink n' Moo Food truck, a place that re-invents Texas barbecue. Danielle whips up the El Diablo, and The Hulky - two monster-sized sandwiches - and ends with the chicken fried brisket. Danielle and barbecue buddy Ernesto Cervantes compete at the Bedford Blues and BBQ Festival. This is Danielle's second time here. Last time, she scored a fourth place in brisket. Can she do it again?

title: BBQ Crawl
desc: Danielle heads south to Lockhart, the birthplace of Texas barbecue. First up is Smitty's Market, a beloved old building that serves up traditional German-style barbecue, which means smoked sausage. After that, Danielle hits up the famous Kreuz Market. Everything about this place is massive - the dining room, the barbecue pits and the portions of pork spare ribs, beans, German potato salad, sauerkraut, and their kickin' new jalapeno cheese sausage. At Kreuz, sauce is not allowed. They believe the meat should stand on its own, and it sure does. Next up is Black's BBQ, the oldest family-owned barbecue joint in Texas. They claim to be the first barbecue joint to put brisket on the menu, but these days they are getting buzz for the giant beef ribs which is what Danielle is here to try. Lastly, it's time to leave Lockhart and dip a bit further south where the roots of Texas barbecue are Spanish. Danielle and her old friend, Robert, take apart a cow head and separate the meat used for Barbacoa. Robert samples the cow's less desirable pieces like the eyeballs and tongue. Danielle sticks to her favourites - crispy beef, tacos, carnitas and, of course, the cow cheek meat used for Barbacoa.

title: Jimmy's Australian Food Adventure
desc: Jimmy Doherty is on the trail of Australia's wild foods. At Adelaide Central Market in South Australia, he has a go at making gourmet kangaroo bangers with farmer Richard Gunner. Aboriginal elder Neville Poelina and his family take him fishing for barramundi at Udialla Springs on the edge of the Western Desert, before Jimmy joins them for an outback supper.

title: The Great Australian Cookbook
desc: Creator of the fine dining institution the Lake House in Daylesford, Victoria, Alla Wolf-Tasker prepares her share platter recipe. Agrarian cook Rodney Dunn showcases his Tasmanian property's produce, baking a rhubarb and berry crumble with goat's milk and vanilla custard for his young family.

title: Jimmy Shu's Taste of the Territory
desc: Jimmy visits the breathtaking landscapes of Kakadu to find out about Top End bush foods that Aboriginal people have been eating for thousands of years. He meets traditional owner Mandy Muir who takes Jimmy to see her country via a boat trip along the spectacular Yellow Waters. Next Jimmy meets young Bininj chef Ben Tyler who runs Kakadu Kitchen.

title: Poh and Co.
desc: The garden is nearing completion and Poh and Jono decide to have a party to say 'thank you' to everyone who helped with the transformation and to christen the new pizza oven. But Poh thinks the outdoor areas lack personality, so armed with custard biscuits, she visits three inspiring gardens. That evening, Poh serves curry puffs to all her favourite people before they tuck into the pizzas, which are a big success. Fast forward three months and Poh is very excited to be cooking with her first crop of tomatoes.

title: Come Dine with Me
desc: Every week, five strangers take it in turns to throw a dinner party. But this is no ordinary supper, as the guests are secretly scoring the host, and at the end of the week the top-scoring host wins 1000 pounds.

title: Come Dine with Me

title: Surfing the Menu: New Zealand
desc: Bender and Mark surf an amazing break on a black volcanic beach. Nearby they help a lobster-man beach his boat with the help of a bulldozer.

title: Oliver's Twist
desc: Jamie caters his friend Peter's birthday party.

title: The Chefs' Line
desc: Watch executive chef Alessandro Pavoni from legendary hatted Italian restaurant Sotto Sopra in Sydney go up against this week's final home cook, Ivano, in the ultimate David versus Goliath battle. Can the passion of a home cook's pasta beat a professional chef at the top of his game?

title: Kriol Kitchen
desc: Drawing back to her grandmother and other family members, Helani will show and teach us how to make some staple dishes that are made every day in the Torres Strait Islander community.

title: Pati's Mexican Table
desc: Pati heads to the coastal city of Champoton, located an hour south of Campeche. With a warm welcome from her friend Chachi, they taste their way through the local market and gather groceries for a family dinner at Hacienda Niop. Pati learns the secrets behind the area's most prized dishes: pibi pollo, a gigantic tamal cooked underground, and pan de cazon, a local version of lasagna made with corn tortillas, dogfish, beans, and spicy tomato sauce. Back in Pati's kitchen, she makes her own version of the giant tamal, a bit simpler but with all the flavour; these little packets are a party on their own. And to finish it off, something sweet and reminiscent of the seaside village, a creamy crema de coco.

title: Carnival Eats
desc: Noah Cappe starts in the Midwest at the Three Rivers Fest, then goes for the gold at the Orange County Fair.

title: River Cottage Australia
desc: Paul welcomes home his jersey cow Bessie but it's not the homecoming he was hoping for - Bessie could be barren. Tomato season has sprung and Paul needs to make the most of his troubled crop. He welcomes two new friends to the farm, with expert passata knowledge passed down by generations. He learns there's more to mushrooms than meets the eye, and takes advantage of the autumn rain by dropping into mate Darcy's to dunk some traps into his dam.

title: Oliver's Twist

title: The Chefs' Line
desc: Judge Melissa Leong takes us inside the kitchen of hatted restaurant Sotto Sopra. Melissa and the chefs' line will reminisce about the week and delve into some delicious new dishes prepared by the line: gamberi e polenta crostino, galletto, tagliolini di montagna, and torta alla patata dolce.

title: Kriol Kitchen
desc: Eric Fejo tells us he is an average cook, but we think he is more than that. In this episode Eric shows us his family recipes for three amazing dishes.

title: Pati's Mexican Table
desc: The Yucatan Peninsula is known for its vast jungles, underground cenotes, pristine beaches, ancient architecture and sensational food. With the help of local friends and chefs, Pedro Evia and David Cetina, Pati gets an insider's look at Merida, the capital of the Yucatan. Pati explores the forefronts of molecular gastronomy, botanas or 'bar snacks' like chaya empanadas filled with gooey Edam cheese at a cantina, family classics like Mondongo stew at the market, and even foreign influences like kibi. One thing is for sure, Merida is a food-lover's city. Back at home, Pati's putting together a Yucatan family classic, pork and beans, perfect for any night of the week, and a mango pound cake that will put a smile on her boys' faces.

title: Carnival Eats
desc: Mr Big Bite Noah Cappe starts the day right at the Shasta District Fair, and takes to the skies at the National Balloon Classic in Iowa.

title: The Cook and the Chef
desc: Simon and Maggie are holding a tea party to celebrate the days when afternoon teas (complete with cakes and cucumber sandwiches) were quite the done thing. In Victorian-era Australia, our eating and drinking habits were still shaped by our ties to Britain, and what could be more British than afternoon tea?

title: The Cook and the Chef
desc: If you fancy some fine French fare, then join Maggie and Simon as they reveal the significant contribution the French have made to the kitchen while tempting you with classics such as bouillabaisse.

title: Donal's Kitchen Hero Feast
desc: Donal visits three of Galway's finest artisan food producers: Connemara Salmon Smokehouse, Connemara Hill Lamb, and Cuinneog Buttermilk. He then prepares the first feast at the spectacularly located Lisdonagh House in Headford, Co Galway.

title: River Cottage Australia
desc: Living so close to the coast has many advantages. Paul learns how to forage for seaside food from a friend, but it's not for free and he faces a chef-style challenge. As a valuable member of the community, Paul is put to task when he helps out the largest fire service in the world, the RFS.

title: Nigella Express
desc: Eating out has never been so easy, because Nigella's got it covered the expressway. She never leaves home without a food parcel, so whenever and wherever you are going, Nigella's got the answer to what to take. For super-fast emergency rations on the run, a delicious sesame noodle salad and a velvety pea and pesto soup that Nigella finds incredibly hard to resist.

title: Paul Hollywood's Pies and Puds
desc: Paul Hollywood celebrates British pies and puds during a day with the ladies of Chippenham Truck Stop, and creates a bacon and egg pie inspired by their surprisingly healthy roadside fare. Chinese chef Andrew Wong is won over by Paul's creation of something that could only exist in Britain: a Chinese chow mein pie.

title: Rick Stein's India
desc: Rick Stein begins his Indian journey by exploring the regions that began Britain's love affair with curry: Bengal and Tamil Nadu. The British influence in Kolkata and Chennai remains strong to this day, and Rick enjoys the prominence of fish and seafood in so many of their dishes - dishes flavoured with mustard in Kolkata and tamarind in Chennai. Exploring the eating habits of these cities is the start of a fascinating trip for Rick, who is inspired to cook dishes like prawns in coconut milk and his mum's version of British raj curry.

title: Milpirri - Winds of Change
desc: It's early October in 2012, and Steve Jampijinpa is leaving Canberra for his home in outback Lajamanu. Once there, he'll play a key part in something very important to him: Milipirri, a biennial community festival of dance, art and ceremony. But things are changing for Steve and his community. This documentary reveals what goes on behind the scenes of a controversial and ground-breaking Walpiri event.

title: Vote Yes For Aborigines
desc: The 1967 referendum resulted in the removal of two sections of the constitution that discriminated against Aborigines. In the referendum, over 90 percent of voters agreed that Aborigines be counted in the census and that the Commonwealth government take charge of Aboriginal affairs, effectively acknowledging Aboriginal people as citizens within their own country.

title: Sweet Country
desc: Set in 1929 in the outback of the Northern Territory, this is the story of a young boy called Philomac, who witnesses Sam, an Aboriginal stockman, kill station owner Harry Marsh in self-defence. Sam and his pregnant wife Lizzie go on the run and a posse pursues them across the outback. The posse don't catch Sam, as he is a clever man and an expert bushman. Eventually, for the health of his pregnant wife, Sam gives himself up. A trial is held in town and when the truth comes out in the courtroom about Sam's actions, he is acquitted. Justice has been served. Philomac and Sam set off on their journey home, but, soon after leaving town, a shot rings out and justice is crushed.

title: Cold Justice

Police believe that she was held captive and kept alive for around 10 days, during which time she was tortured and sexually abused before being killed. Six months later, bush hikers stumble across Lois' skeletal remains.

title: BBQ Crawl
desc: Kansas is known for bison, so that's what Danielle is out to find. At Public at the Brickyard, they serve up tasty bison burgers complete with crushed espresso seasoning and chipotle aioli. While they're fairly new, they already have a loyal following. Then, it's off to the Indian Creek Bison Ranch to see these beasts in person. Rancher Jerry Schmidt takes Danielle in the back of his pickup truck to give her a tour of the acreage, teach her about the Native American culture in the area and how bison play a part in this region. Danielle and barbecue buddies, Andy and Kim Groneman, compete at the Sky's the Limit BBQ Classic in Garden City, Kansas. This is a super small contest, with only 15 teams. This is a welcome change from Danielle's usual 50 to 100 team contests; this contest is small but mighty. Danielle takes a risk by switching up her pork recipe.

title: BBQ Crawl
desc: Danielle heads to Jet BBQ in Wichita, Kansas. Located in a historical firehouse, this is a true drive-thru - drive in one door, order your goods, and drive out. Danielle orders up The Dave - a delicious sandwich filled with beans, brisket and sausage. Then, she caps it off with a joyride in a fire truck. Danielle crosses into Oklahoma and heads to an ol' fashioned cattle auction. Farming is big in Oklahoma and these guys know how to pick their beef. Danielle sits in at a live auction, meets some real-life cowboys and talks to the auctioneer who gives her a lesson in 'auction talk.' After that, it's off to Leo's BBQ: an old, converted gas station that churns out smoked bologna, hot links, and their famous strawberry banana cake. This place has it all. The charm, the service, the flavour. It fills up quickly, but worth the wait. The last stop in Oklahoma is Van's Pig Stand, the oldest barbecue joint in Oklahoma. Danielle helps herself to their famous pig sandwich, two pieces of buttered toast piled high with tender, smokey cubes of pork. It's love at first bite.

title: Rick Stein's India
desc: Rick Stein begins his Indian journey by exploring the regions that began Britain's love affair with curry: Bengal and Tamil Nadu. The British influence in Kolkata and Chennai remains strong to this day, and Rick enjoys the prominence of fish and seafood in so many of their dishes - dishes flavoured with mustard in Kolkata and tamarind in Chennai. Exploring the eating habits of these cities is the start of a fascinating trip for Rick, who is inspired to cook dishes like prawns in coconut milk and his mum's version of British raj curry.

But the discovery of two bodies on the shores of the lake where Margot was killed forces the police to reopen the case, with new evidence casting suspicion on Alex. At the same time, Dr Beck is receiving strange email messages - from his presumably dead wife.

Travelling to the Gold Coast they catch up with Australia's former strongest man, but things turn surreal when they get embroiled in a car-flipping contest. And their mission to take the Aussie on at their own barbecue game stalls - because of their broken-down van.

title: Cheese Slices
desc: Roquefort is the most significant of all blue cheeses, it's one of the world's oldest cheeses and one of the few blue cheeses still made from raw milk. To find out what's changed since his last visit to the famous village of Roquefort-sur-Soulzon, Will and Ellie catch up with the makers of Papillon Roquefort, one of the most respected and well-known export brands from the region. Another of the finest boutique Roquefort producers is Carles, and Will takes Ellie into the company's iconic limestone caves to speak to Delphine Carles and sample some of her delectable blue cheeses.

title: Cheese Slices
desc: Under the spotlight in this episode is gorgonzola, the grandaddy of all European blue cheeses made from cow's milk, and its cousin cave-ripened taleggio, which until recently was one of Italy's great soft cheese secrets. Cheese authority Will Studd travels to Northern Italy to see how and where these fascinating cheeses are created. He visits Lombardy, and the maze of underground cellars in the town of Novara where more than 70 percent of gorgonzola is matured. Then it's off to the foothills of the Alps, where caves cooled by melting snow are still used to ripen taleggio the old-fashioned way by the Mauri family.

title: Secret Meat Business
desc: Malaysian cooking is a cuisine that melds Chinese, Indian and traditional Malay flavours. Adrian pays homage to his time spent there as a child by preparing mouth-watering beef rendang.

title: The Cook and the Chef
desc: Chefs love working with colour and contrast, but Maggie and Simon love a challenge so this week they're going blonde. White asparagus, light coloured meats, garlic, white chocolate, coconut and meringue all make the 'blonde food' menu, and with the use of simple sauces and balancing of flavours the cook and the chef prove that blonde doesn't mean bland. It's a program packed with blonde tips and worth watching just to see how the theme goes to Simon's head.

title: The Cook and the Chef
desc: When offal is mentioned, most of us think of the internal organs of animals, but the word also refers to anything that is considered worthless or thrown away. This episode, Maggie and Simon demonstrate that some ingredients which are considered 'junk food' can be tasty if they're prepared with love and attention.

title: The Cook and the Chef
desc: It's the middle of spring and the sunshine and longer days are a great excuse for people to get together and enjoy good company and good food. In this program, Maggie and Simon whip up dishes that'll not only impress the crowd but are easy to transport to any get-together. Maggie's 'moveable feast' is a creamy asparagus and leek tart, a whole meal encased in a sour cream pastry and ready to go. Simon shows us how to make a beautifully textured goat cheese lasagne that can be transported using a gourmet 'must-have', the cardboard box.

title: Donal's Kitchen Hero Feast
desc: With Christmas fast approaching, Donal visits a turkey farm and a bakery selling mince pies. The garden florists in the Powerscourt Centre will be showing Donal how to decorate a table at Christmas.

title: Jimmy Shu's Taste of the Territory
desc: Jimmy tastes some of Darwin's most popular street food from the stalls of the Parap Saturday market. Jimmy talks about Darwin's laksa obsession, and visits Mary's Laksa - a stall who have been serving laska for over 20 yeas.

title: Diana's Asia Unplated
desc: Southern Indian cooking is distinctly influenced by the abundance of fresh fruit and vegetables found in the region. Sarah Todd's love of Indian cuisine has led her to open up restaurants in Goa and Mumbai, documented on the television series, My Restaurant in India. Sarah starts with vindaloo pork ribs topped with Goan bhel, before cooking a vegetarian dish of baked cauliflower with pineapple sansav. Diana finishes the theme with a traditional dessert called sweet appam, filled with carmelised banana, the perfect snack on a balmy afternoon.

title: Bonacini's Italy
desc: Simplicity is key with Sicilian cuisine and Michael explores just how the region balances simplicity with intensity through four flavourful dishes. He starts with an antipasto of folded flatbread with ricotta and fennel seeds, and a primo of broccoli and sausage rigatoni.

title: Rick Stein's Far Eastern Odyssey
desc: One of Britain's most revered chefs and successful authors, Rick Stein sets off on an epic culinary journey to explore the far east's most diverse food cultures, which have soared to the heights of popularity the world over. Rick begins his odyssey in Cambodia, a country still recovering from the regime of the Khmer Rouge. Rick discovers the joys of freshly caught swimmer crabs cooked with green peppercorns from Kampot, once the king of pepper. He learns how to cook the most famous dish in the country, fish amok, made with lemongrass and coconut. He also samples lok lak, an extremely popular and delicious dish made with stir-fried strips of marinated beef.

title: Jonathan Phang's Gourmet Express
desc: Starting in Australia's thriving cosmopolitan west coast city of Perth, Jonathan lives like a true Aussie when he cooks prawns on the barbie with chef Russell Blaikie, gets a little pick-me-up when he samples an espresso martini, and pays homage to the area's printing press history with chef Shane Watson's black and white menu.

title: The Sweet Life With Elise Strachan
desc: Elise is joined in the kitchen by My Kitchen Rules 2016 winners Tasia and Gracia Seger, who put a unique Indonesian spin on the French classic: brulee. Culinary artist Siew Heng Boon shares an epic Malaysian jelly cake recipe, while chef Phi Nguyen serves up a Japanese frosty favourite: kakigori. Yasoda Welsh makes Indian-inspired hand-painted mandala cheesecakes.

title: Destination Flavour Scandinavia
desc: Adam is in the Swedish city of Malmo to visit the kitchen of the first Swedish female chef, Titti Qvarnstrom, awarded a Michelin star for her restaurant Bloom in the Park. Adam visits a school where they have introduced a city-wide organic food policy and makes pea soup and spelt pancakes for the kids. Adam takes in a new Swedish project called Hoffice, which turns apartments into temporary co-working spaces, and Adam makes delicious semlor in the home-office kitchen.

title: Comfort Eating
